## When to use this component

The error component is used to wrap form inputs and fieldsets to to show validation errors.

## How to use this component

Generally speaking you should not need to {{
    onsExternalLink({
        "url": "https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/templating.html#call",
        "linkText": "call"
    })
}} `onsError` yourself as it is already called from within form input components. However if you need to create a pattern or component that requires a error you can use {{
    onsExternalLink({
        "url": "https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/templating.html#call",
        "linkText": "nunjucks' call functionality"
    })
}} `onsError`.

| Name       | Type    | Required | Description                                                                                                                               |
| ---------- | ------- | -------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| text       | string  | true     | The text describing the error                                                                                                             |
| id         | string  | true     | The HTML `id` attribute that the [error summary](/patterns/correct-errors/#error-summary) link can anchor to                              |
| attributes | object  | false    | HTML attributes (for example, data attributes) to add to the field                                                                        |
| dsExample  | boolean | false    | Set to `true` if using component as an example in the Design System. Prevents focus on error on page load. *Only for use in DS examples*  |

